{"id":52,"parent_id":50,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":52,"title":"Luke 2: The Savior Is Born","subtitle":"","short_title":"Luke 2: The Savior Is Born","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born"},[".heading",{"id":"head3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.head3"},["h1","Luke 2"],[".subtitle","The Savior Is Born"],[".",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-054-1.gif"}]],[".intro","Luke is the only gospel writer to tell us about many of the details of the birth of Jesus Christ. These include the taxing by Caesar, the journey of Mary and Joseph to Bethlehem, the birth in a stable, the shepherds and the angels, Simeon and Anna, and Jesus teaching at the temple. Why do you think Luke would want his gentile friend Theophilus to know these things?"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2"},"Luke 2"]],["p.para",{"id":"p62","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p62"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.1-39"},"Luke 2:1–39"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.18-25"},"Matthew 1:18–25"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.f9"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2"},"Luke 2"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Be delivered"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Have her baby"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Swaddling clothes"],"(vv. 7, 12)"],["td","Strips of cloth wrapped around the baby"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Manger"],"(vv. 7, 12)"],["td","A feeding place for animals"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Good tidings"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Good news"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Haste"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Speed"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Consolation of Israel"],"(v. 25)"],["td","Comfort or relief of Israel, meaning the Messiah"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","From her virginity"],"(v. 36)"],["td","After her marriage"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fourscore and four years"],"(v. 37)"],["td","Eighty-four years (one score is twenty years)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Redemption"],"(v. 38)"],["td","Deliverance; to be saved from the consequences of sin"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fulfilled the days"],"(v. 43)"],["td","Stayed until the celebration was over"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Kinsfolk and acquaintance"],"(v. 44)"],["td","Family and friends"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Subject"],"(v. 51)"],["td","Obedient; followed the advice and counsel of"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Stature"],"(v. 52)"],["td","Size and appearance"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.21"},"Luke 2:21"],"—“When Eight Days Were Accomplished”"],["p.para",{"id":"p76","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p76"},"As a sign of the covenant the Lord made with Abraham and his descendants, all male children of the house of Israel were to be circumcised when they were eight days old (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/17.12"},"Genesis 17:12"],"; Bible Dictionary,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/circumcision"},"“circumcision,”"],"p. 646)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.22"},"Luke 2:22"],"—“The Days of Her Purification”"],["p.para",{"id":"p77","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p77"},"The mother of a newborn son was considered unclean (meaning she was unable to participate in the ordinances of the law of Moses) for forty days. After forty days she could go to the temple and offer sacrifice for her purification."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.46-47"},"Luke 2:46–47"],"—Jesus Teaches in the Temple"],["p.para",{"id":"p78","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p78"},"The Joseph Smith Translation tells us that the teachers were asking the questions, not Jesus (see JST,Luke 2:46). Those teachers were surprised “at his understanding and answers” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.47"},"Luke 2:47"],")."]],[".",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-055-1.gif"}]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.52"},"Luke 2:52"],"—Jesus’ Development in His Youth"],["p.para",{"id":"p79","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p79"},"Speaking about",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.52"},"Luke 2:52"],", President Ezra Taft Benson taught: “The most successful program of complete youth fitness ever known to man was described in fourteen words. … There is the ideal of any program of youth fitness, to help our youth increase in wisdom and stature and in favor with God and man. It covers everything—physical fitness, mental fitness, social fitness, emotional fitness, and spiritual fitness” (",["span.emphasis","The Teachings of Ezra Taft Benson,"],"555–56)."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p80","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p80"},"Do activities A and C or only activity B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2"},"Luke 2"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"The Christmas Story"],[".figure",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.f11"},["p.preamble",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2"},"Luke 2"],"contains one of the most beautiful and well-known accounts in the Bible. After carefully reading",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.1-16"},"Luke 2:1–16"],", do the following:"],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Make up a quiz with at least six questions that cover what you think are the most important details of Jesus’ birth. In parenthesis after each question, write the correct answer and the verse where the answer can be found."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","List five phrases from",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.1-16"},"Luke 2:1–16"],"that you think would be good titles for a talk about Jesus at Christmastime."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Witnesses of the Christ Child"],["p.para",{"id":"p83","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p83"},"Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2"},"Luke 2"],"and list everyone mentioned in this chapter who saw Jesus. Next to each name list how they came to know about Jesus."]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-c.gif"}],"A Pattern for Personal Growth"],["p.para",{"id":"p84","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-2-the-savior-is-born.p84"},"After reading",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.40,49-52"},"Luke 2:40, 49–52"],", list the different areas in which Jesus grew and developed. How could you “grow and develop” in those areas?"]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
